added.title: A Quiet Delivery
added.description: Thomas volunteers to get a sleeping Annie and Clarabel across Sodor without waking them up, only to discover that it's going to be harder than he imagined.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Kana Goes Slow
added.description: When Kana's power goes out during a delivery run, Thomas teaches her that sometimes it's okay to go slow.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Rain, Rain Go Away
added.description: After Grumpy's anger sends his belly badge out of control with a thunderstorm that floods a newly-planted Whiffle meadow, he vows to never be grumpy again. Renaming himself "Mr. Happy," he drives everyone crazy with niceness. When the Whiffles desperately need his clouds to make rain and Mr. Happy can't deliver, Cheer and the team must get him back in touch with his inner grump.

added.title: Boo
added.description: Lucas discovers that it's best to ask your friends permission before you give them a scare on Halloween. He adopts the guise of a ghost and the use of decorative masks and sneaky hiding places to give them all the jumps.

added.title: Race the Beast
added.description: Mush-Mush and his friends are determined to win the bark sledge race, but their essential fourth team member drops out. Our friends ask Mushpot to step up from being their coach to racing with them. The Mushelder is reluctant at first but soon reveals the tough competitor he is!

added.title: Plays Baby/Flies on a Plane/In the Bathtub/Goes Birdwatching/The Doll
added.description: Caillou thinks his sister Rosie is getting favorable treatment./It's Caillou's first flight./It's bathtime, and for Caillou that means trouble./Grandma always has the best surprises./Mom is putting on her makeup to go out with Dad.

added.title: Ducks
added.description: Meet Bing and his friends… Join us and celebrate the noisy, joyful, messy reality of preschool life.

added.title: Fetch Loula Fetch!
added.description: Pocoyo and Loula are going to the beach, but they keep losing their ball. They learn about colors, shapes and sizes as they meet their friends along the way.

added.title: School Daze
added.description: The babies play pretend school in preparation for the real thing.

added.title: Waffle Cones for Whiffles
added.description: The Whiffles are too hot and tired to work because their daily treat, colorful ice in Waffles Cones delivered by the whimsical "Icelings," hasn't arrived - the Icelings have mysteriously disappeared. As the Care Bears search for them, Share volunteers to make the treats. It's much more than she can handle but she's determined to go-it-alone and not ask for help. Things get out of hand and Share ends up snared in Bluster's trap with the Icelings, who help her to realize that we get more done when we work together.

added.title: Never Boop a Robot
added.description: When Lucas sees a robot on the shelf he boops it. This sets off the clockwork mechanism and now Lucas is pursued around the house by a B Movie robot. When Bodhi gets cornered, Lucas realizes he's got to help his friend.

added.title: Mushlers to the Rescue
added.description: Having rescued a Mushlet, Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit become heroes in Mushton, and they're loving it! So Mushlers create a rescue team but alas, no one needs saving! How can you be a hero when there is nothing to be heroic about? Then when some Mushlets become adrift on the river, Team Mush-Mush, with Morel's help, have to save the day again.

added.title: Looks for Gilbert/Surprise Breakfast/Missing Sock/Goes to Work/Quarrel
added.description: Caillou is having a game of dinosaur hunter with Gilbert the cat./Caillou gets up early one morning./Caillou wants to wear his favorite socks, but one of them is missing./Caillou goes to work with Mom./Clementine comes over to play.

added.title: Things That Go Bugs in the Night
added.description: Bugs must find the courage to discover what's making scary noises outside.

added.title: Smoothie
added.description: Meet Bing and his friends… Join us and celebrate the noisy, joyful, messy reality of preschool life.

added.title: A Little Cloud
added.description: Pocoyo has an unusual new friend: a lonely little cloud who just wants to play.

added.title: The Joke is on Thomas
added.description: When Thomas and Percy's plan to surprise Diesel goes awry, the two friends still manage to cheer up Diesel... just not in the way they expected!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: The Art of Friendship
added.description: When Chanterelle sees how good Lilit is at painting, she offers to help her dig into her talent. But Lilit's art lessons conflict with the fun project she has been working on with Mush-Mush and Chep. And when she sees that her friends are having a great time without her, Lilit is seriously annoyed which her paintings start showing.

added.title: The Rollinator
added.description: Chep is so good at moss-marbles, no one wants to play him anymore! No one except Sumush who reveals himself to be a tough competitor. To Chep's disbelief, Sumush keeps on winning. But Lilit and Mush-Mush convince their friend not to give up. Chep decides to play his favourite moss-marble: the Rollinator. The one marble he never risked playing before.

added.title: Hula Hoop
added.description: Coco is showing Bing her new Holly Hula Hoop, but will be Bing be able to hula like Coco?

added.title: Noise to My Ears
added.description: Pocoyo, Elly and Baby Bird have great fun making lots of noise. But what's music to their ears is a real old racket to poor Pato who's trying to have a nap. Pocoyo, Elly and Baby Bird agree to try to be more considerate. But then they find another wonderful way to make music - by bouncing balls. Again, their music wakes up the sleepy duck. Finally Pocoyo and his chums make a cacophony with lots of machines. Pato completely loses his cool. Pocoyo's attempt at a soothing lullaby does nothing to calm the ever-more exhausted quacker. Pato realizes there's no other way round this - he's going to have to conduct them himself. In so doing, he really gets into it and the music gives him lots of energy. He's no longer sleepy and everyone's playing brilliant harmonious music together.

added.title: Caillou's Water Park/Gone Fishing/The Water Goes 'Round/Caillou's Test Drive/A Very Good Swimmer!
added.description: Caillou learns that the best fun is made up and not bought and paid for./Caillou learns about patience when he goes fishing with Daddy and Grandpa at the pier./Grandma is watching Caillou for the day, and he wants her to play trucks with him./When their car breaks down, the family goes shopping for a new one./Caillou gets an introduction to what it means to be handicapped, when, at the pool, he meets Tammy.

added.title: Take Us Out to the Ballgame
added.description: The Baby Looney Tunes experience their very first big stadium baseball game. Lola's favorite team's star batter gets her undivided attention until Lola's coaching affects the very outcome of the contest.

added.title: Clues Encounters of the Tweety Kind
added.description: Tweety feels neglected when no one wants him on their museum scavenger hunt team. Using his innate sleuthing abilities and the help of a friendly museum guard, Tweety proves to be the best scavenger hunter of them all. Once Tweety wins the contest, everyone wants him on their team.

removed.title: Swept Away
removed.description: Pocoyo shows us that tidying can be fun too: a broom can be a horse, a guitar, or even a hockey stick!

removed.title: Swing
removed.description: Meet Bing and his friends… Join us and celebrate the noisy, joyful, messy reality of preschool life.

removed.title: Like a Duck to Water
removed.description: Daffy overcomes his fear of the swimming pool.

removed.title: Oh My Compost
removed.description: When Sushi-Mushi breaks the only spoon he has ever cooked with, he declares his cooking days are over! So Mush-Mush and friends step up to cook for everyone instead. How hard can it be? It turns out, very! The Mushlers will have to convince Sushi-Mushi he's still the best compost chef, even without his favorite spoon!

removed.title: Finding Posada
removed.description: When Victor and Valentino attempt to win the grand prize of best ofrenda at the Dia de Muertos festival, they enlist the help of legendary artist Jose Guadalupe Posada himself!

removed.title: Ghost Camp
removed.description: Lucas and his friends are camping in the garden. Avocado tells them all a spooky story around the campfire. This makes Lucas really uneasy and he thinks there's a ghostie in the garden.

removed.title: A Yoorg Awakening
removed.description: Funshine's jokes unwittingly hurt the feelings of a strange Rock Giant. Disturbed from its slumber, the usually benign creature inadvertently creates havoc for the Whiffles until Funshine calms it by apologizing.

removed.title: Big Jumping Spider
removed.description: When Findley comments to Lucas that his jump isn't very long or high Lucas ramps things up, jumping higher and longer in ever increasing death defying jumps. Findley is now beginning to regret his comment and wishes Lucas wouldn't jump so far. This all culminates in Lucas going for the big one in his car down a track. Can Findley convince him not too?

removed.title: Blocks
removed.description: Meet Bing and his friends… Join us and celebrate the noisy, joyful, messy reality of preschool life.

removed.title: Comfort Level
removed.description: Sylvester learns to live without his blankey.

removed.title: Rules of the Game
removed.description: When Thomas builds an obstacle course for his friends, he gets upset when they won't play with it HIS way.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: License to Deliver
removed.description: When Percy has to deliver a new light bulb to the lighthouse at night, Thomas suggests playing secret agents along the way to help Percy forget about his fear of the dark.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Fly, Chase, Fly
removed.description: Chep is disappointed Mush-Mush and Lilit are too busy leaf-gliding to play moss-ball with him, so he hangs out with a new weevil friend instead. But Chep's new friend must migrate with all the other weevils. Except he doesn't know how to fly! Chep must teach him to fly while overcoming his own secret fear of heights.

removed.title: Who's on the Phone?
removed.description: Pocoyo finds a phone. He has to work out what it's for, and who's on the other end of the line. It's Elly inviting everyone to a party!

removed.title: Nobody's Perfect
removed.description: When Cheer makes some simple mistakes, she begins to lose confidence in her piloting skills and herself. The self-doubt becomes so severe, she decides to step away from her role as pilot of the Cloudseeker. But the Team needs her, the Whiffles need her, and she must regain her self-confidence so they can stop Bluster's latest nefarious scheme.

removed.title: Patolli
removed.description: When Valentino's has a hot winning streak at an ancient board game, his beginner's luck gets the best of him until, he meets his match. Will he reign as champion or lose it all?
